In England, in the seven days to 14 March, there were 32,836 new confirmed cases (58.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 March, there were 33,644 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 2% (808 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 19 March is 3,750,089 (6,662.4 cases per 100,000 population).
